## Architecture Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as User A (Caller)
    participant GW as WS Gateway
    participant RED as Redis Cluster
    participant KFK as Kafka
    participant GW2 as WS Gateway (Pod Y)
    participant B as User B (Callee)

    A->>GW: call:initiate {targetUserId, callType}
    GW->>RED: Rate limit check
    GW->>RED: Check active calls (isUserInCall)
    GW->>GW: Authorization (blocks, privacy, spam)
    GW->>RED: Presence lookup (resolveUserLocation)
    GW->>RED: Create call state (Lua: INITIATING)
    GW->>RED: Transition INITIATING → SIGNALING
    GW->>RED: PUBLISH signal:userB
    RED-->>GW2: Signal delivered
    GW2->>B: call:signal {CALL_INCOMING}
    GW->>RED: Transition SIGNALING → RINGING
    B->>GW2: call:accept {callId}
    GW2->>RED: Lua CAS: RINGING → ACCEPTED
    GW2->>RED: PUBLISH signal:userA
    RED-->>GW: Signal delivered
    GW->>A: call:signal {CALL_ACCEPTED}
    A->>GW: webrtc:offer {sdp}
    GW->>RED: PUBLISH signal:userB
    RED-->>GW2: Signal delivered
    GW2->>B: call:signal {WEBRTC_OFFER}
    B->>GW2: webrtc:answer {sdp}
    GW2->>RED: Transition CONNECTING → ICE_NEGOTIATION
    GW2->>RED: Flush ICE buffer
    GW2->>RED: PUBLISH signal:userA
    RED-->>GW: Signal delivered
    GW->>A: call:signal {WEBRTC_ANSWER}
    Note over A,B: ICE candidates exchanged via same Redis pub/sub path
    A->>GW: call:connected {callId}
    GW->>RED: Transition ICE_NEGOTIATION → CONNECTED
    Note over A,B: P2P media (DTLS-SRTP) or via TURN relay
```

---

## Key Implementation Details

### 1. Atomic State Machine (Lua Scripts)

Three Redis Lua scripts handle all critical state transitions:
- **`LUA_CREATE_CALL`** — atomic call creation + simultaneous-call lock
- **`LUA_ACCEPT_CALL`** — CAS for double-accept prevention (RINGING→ACCEPTED only)
- **`LUA_TRANSITION_STATE`** — generic CAS with version counter bump

### 2. Cross-Region Signaling

When User A is in `us-east` and User B is in `ap-south`:
1. Gateway Pod → Kafka `signaling.cross-region` topic
2. MirrorMaker 2 replicates to `ap-south` Kafka
3. [SignalConsumer](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/signaling/signal.consumer.ts#22-87) in `ap-south` picks it up
4. Delivers to User B via local Redis pub/sub

### 3. TURN Credentials

- HMAC-SHA1 compatible with coturn's `use-auth-secret` mode
- Per-user allocation limits (max 2 concurrent)
- Load-aware geo-selection with circuit breaker fallback

### 4. Graceful Shutdown

On `SIGTERM`:
1. Stop call auditor
2. Emit `system:reconnect` with staggered delays (1-5s)
3. Wait up to 15s for active calls to drain
4. Force-disconnect remaining sockets
5. Cleanup pod presence from Redis
6. Close Fastify + Redis

### 5. Rate Limiting

| Event | Limit |
|-------|-------|
| `call:initiate` | 1 per 5s |
| `webrtc:offer` | 1 per 10s |
| `ice-candidate` | 50 per 30s |
| [heartbeat](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/call/call.state-machine.ts#241-248) | 1 per 25s |
| SDP payload | max 10KB |
| ICE payload | max 1KB |
